Subject: Task Frame Launch Queue

Description: Contract for preparing inspectable task-frame launch candidates before any LM Studio or worker lane execution.

@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\source_documents\2026-06-24_task_frame_launch_queue\Derived_Task_Frame_Launch_Queue_Source.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SOPTaskManager.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\LMStudioWorkerFunctionalLane.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SemanticCognitionOperatingLoop.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\spool\WorkerLanes.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\task_queues\2026-06-24_lmstudio_limited_worker_pilot_queue_001.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\CodexLMStudioOrchestrationWorkspace.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\CodexConversationAgentSpawnNode.sop
@ [source] C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\platform\SOPJobNodeBrowserInterface.sop

& [TaskFrameLaunchQueue] is the inspectable queue layer between task_frame readiness and worker launch
  + [pattern_role] is task_frame_to_worker_launch_queue_membrane
  + [queue_authority] is Codex, which owns queue creation, launch inspection, execution, capture, validation, integration, commits, and pushes
  + [task_frame_candidate] is one task frame with objective, reminders, lane fit, gates, launch policy, capture target, outside, and block reasons
  + [queue_status] is empty, queued, ready_for_inspection, blocked, running, completed, or closed
  + [launch_policy] is inspect_before_launch and no_silent_launch
  + [lane_fit] is lm_studio_cli, codex_cli, openai_codex, manual, deferred, or outside
  + [reminder_bundle] is subject_reminder, boundary_reminder, operation_reminder, evidence_reminder, return_reminder, and outside_reminder
  + [gate_set] is sop_language_primer_gate, scratch_isolation_gate, capture_gate, validator_gate, codex_review_gate, and action_gate
  + [capture_target] is the file where raw worker output or blocked result must be stored
  + [launch_result] is the captured returned, validated, rejected, or blocked outcome after Codex chooses to launch a candidate
  + [queue_outside] is automatic launch, hidden model state, worker file mutation, credentials, project-root authority, destructive action, and unrelated dirty files
  + [first_synthesis_backed_pilot_queue] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\events\task_queues\2026-06-24_lmstudio_limited_worker_pilot_queue_001.sop
  + [codex_lmstudio_orchestrator_queue] is C:\Project\Pinky\.sop\workspaces\codex_lmstudio_orchestrator\Queue.sop
  + [lm_studio_manager_candidate] is an LM Studio launch candidate that returns codex_job_proposal text instead of performing repo work
  + [openai_codex_dispatch_candidate] is an OpenAI Codex CLI launch candidate created only after Codex accepts a manager proposal
  + [spawn_node_worker_candidate] is a CodexConversationAgentSpawnNode worker candidate with role, context fit, provider fit, cost, stop, capture, and authority gates
  + [browser_queue_surface] is the read-first SOPJobNodeBrowserInterface view of candidate status, block reasons, gates, launch command, capture target, and outside

  ? [use_when: a task frame is ready enough to become a visible worker-launch candidate]
    = activate [TaskFrameLaunchQueue]

  = must: create or update queue records before launching a worker
  = must: keep every candidate inspectable with launch command, capture target, gates, and block reasons
  = must: classify launch candidates as ready_for_inspection only when no block_reason is active
  = must: preserve outside even when a candidate is ready_for_inspection
  = must: keep LM Studio candidates scratch-isolated, prompt-only, captured, and validator-gated
  = must: route project-root LM Studio candidates to blocked or diagnostic_only until leakage is solved
  = must: let Codex decide whether a ready candidate is actually launched
  = must: treat LM Studio manager candidates as proposal-generating candidates, not implementation candidates
  = must: require Codex launch review before converting a manager proposal into an OpenAI Codex dispatch candidate
  = must: require CodexConversationAgentSpawnNode candidates to expose root submission, Codex app conversation attachment, role, context fit, cost, stop, capture, and authority gates
  = must: expose queue candidates to SOPJobNodeBrowserInterface as inspectable view state, not launch permission
  = must: record launch_result after any launched candidate returns or blocks
  - never: launch a candidate merely because it is queued
  - never: treat ready_for_inspection as worker completion
  - never: give LM Studio worker output file mutation or integration authority

& [TaskFrameLaunchCandidate] is one queued launch candidate
  + [candidate_id] is the stable candidate identifier
  + [task_frame_id] is the task frame this launch candidate serves
  + [task_subject] is the subject held by the frame reminders
  + [objective] is the bounded worker objective
  + [lane_fit] is the selected lane
  + [launch_mode] is scratch_prompt_only, isolated, project_root_diagnostic, manual, or deferred
  + [prompt_packet] is the packet or source record sent to the worker if launched
  + [launch_command] is inspectable proposed command or blocked note
  + [capture_target] is where worker output must be captured before validation
  + [validation_profile] is the expected node, required fields, required terms, and forbidden terms used by Codex-side validation
  + [required_gates] is the gate set that must be satisfied before integration
  + [block_reasons] is active reasons the candidate must not launch
  + [status] is proposed, queue_ready, blocked, deferred, launched, returned, validated, rejected, or integrated
  + [candidate_outside] is hidden model state, automatic launch, worker mutation authority, and unvalidated output

  = must: hold task_frame, objective, lane_fit, launch_mode, prompt_packet, launch_command, capture_target, validation_profile, gates, block_reasons, and outside together
  = must: expose why a candidate is blocked or ready
  = must: stay non-mutating until Codex explicitly launches and validates it
  - never: infer launch, completion, or integration from queue status alone

& [TaskFrameLaunchResult] is the captured outcome for one launched candidate
  + [candidate_id] is the candidate that was launched or blocked
  + [result_file] is the captured worker output, blocked record, or validation report
  + [exit_code] is the worker process exit code or blocked
  + [validation_score] is the Codex-side validator score when output exists
  + [validation_band] is strong, usable, weak, failed, or blocked
  + [integration_disposition] is accept_as_proposal_not_integrated, integrate, retry, reject, blocked, or preserve_outside
  + [result_outside] is stderr warnings, hidden state, unvalidated authority, worker mutation, and broader competence claims

  = must: keep validation distinct from integration
  = must: preserve raw output before review
  = must: route accepted output through Codex review before task narrative integration
  - never: call a validated proposal integrated until Codex records the integration disposition

(task_frame_launch_queue) :task_frame_candidate: /gate_set and launch_policy/ |queue_outside|
  + [task_frame_candidate] is a task frame prepared for worker-lane inspection
  + [gate_set] is primer, isolation, capture, validator, Codex review, and action gates
  + [launch_policy] is inspect_before_launch and no_silent_launch
  |queue_outside| automatic launch, worker mutation, project-root leakage, credentials, destructive action, and unrelated dirty files

/ [task_frame], [lane_fit], [reminder_bundle] -(Queues)> [task_frame_candidate], [launch_command], [capture_target], [queue_outside]
* [task_frame_candidate], [gate_set], [block_reasons] -(Classifies)> [queue_status], [ready_for_inspection], [blocked]
* [ready_for_inspection], [CodexReview], [LMStudioWorkerFunctionalLane] -(MayLaunch)> [captured_output], [validator], [launch_result]
